API Gateway → routes everything
    ↓
Auth Service → handles logins
Patient Service → manages patient data
Billing Service → deals with money stuff
Analytics Service → crunches numbers

Tech I'm Using

Spring Boot 3.x - main framework
Java 17+ - because why not use modern Java
Spring Cloud Gateway - for the API gateway
gRPC - fast inter-service communication
PostgreSQL - main database (MySQL works too)
JWT - authentication tokens
Maven - dependency management
Docker - containerization

Running Without Docker
If you don't want to use Docker:
bash# Start each service in separate terminals
cd auth-service && mvn spring-boot:run
cd patient-service && mvn spring-boot:run
cd billing-service && mvn spring-boot:run
cd analytics-service && mvn spring-boot:run
cd api-gateway && mvn spring-boot:run

Configuration
Create a .env file for each service. Here's what you need:
propertiesDB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=patient_management
DB_USERNAME=your_username
DB_PASSWORD=your_password

JWT_SECRET=make_this_something_secure
JWT_EXPIRATION=86400000

# Ports for each service
AUTH_SERVICE_PORT=8081
PATIENT_SERVICE_PORT=8082
BILLING_SERVICE_PORT=8083
ANALYTICS_SERVICE_PORT=8084
API_GATEWAY_PORT=8080


Project Layout
Patient-Management/
├── api-gateway/          → Gateway service
├── auth-service/         → Authentication
├── patient-service/      → Patient management
├── billing-service/      → Billing and payments
├── analytics-service/    → Analytics and reports
├── infrastructure/       → Docker stuff
├── integration-tests/    → Test suite
└── api-requests/         → Sample API calls
